{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce MPs to represent the interests of British citizens living abroad.",
        "additional_details": "I would like the government to create a seat  or seats for new MPs to represent UK expats living abroad so we are properly represented in parliament and so that democracy is upheld.\r\nAlthough we still have voting rights in the UK, the MPs of our last residence address do not have specific interest in our different circumstances abroad.\r\nThis would be a second attempt for a predictably higher support since the UK is no longer in the EU",
        "background": "Ex-pats abroad need specific support in parliament to represent their interests. Particularly in regard to maintaining their pension rights, their tax status, their voting rights etc particularly since the Uk is no longer in the EU",
